Pick your partywith care for the primary’s sake

Pennsylvania is a closed pri-
mary state. What this means is
that you can only vote in the pri-
mary for the political party in
which you are registered.

Closed primaries are a great
part of the political system in that
they keep voters quasi-ethical. In
states with open primaries, those
states in which you can vote in
whichever party’s primary you
would like, often face the prob-
lem of voters who are registered
with one party storming the polls
of the other party. What this
means is: say Candidate X is a
sure thing to win the Republican
primary. So, a large number of

Republican voters vote in the
Democratic primary for the weak-
est candidate, Candidate Y, who is
the most likely to be beaten by
Candidate X. This destroys the
competition between the parties.
If you are going to register
with a particular party, then, you
should feel at least some loyalty

' to and afﬁliation with that party.

Primaries are the opportunity to
make sure that the best candidate
from your party is on the ballot in
the general election. A Democrat
should be concerned with having
a good Democratic candidate on

 

the ballot, and a Republican
should want a good Republican
candidate on the ballot. Once the
Democrats have chosen their can-
didate and the Republicans have
chosen theirs, then you have the
opportunity to cross party lines.
Those Democrats who didn’t like
Bill Clinton had the opportunity
to vote for another Democratic
candidate in the primary and then
to vote for Bob Dole in the gener-
al election if they so desired.

I That’s the way the system works,

and thought it may not be perfect,
it is the best that we have.

Get out there and register to
vote. Pick your party with care. A
party affiliationqis something that
should be thought over extensive-
ly. Don’t register with a party
simply because it’s the one your
parents favor, your boyfriend
thinks is best, or a TV commer-
cial told you to. Choose it
because it means something to
you and because you think it will
yield the best candidates for
ofﬁce. If you already have a party
afﬁliation but wish to change it,
all you have to do is re—register.
Political parties are the backbone
of our system. Take yours seri-
ously.

